Subject: [PATCH] fix: unbreak Vercel deploy + reposition site honestly as
 pre-launch pilot recruitment
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Deploy/build fixes:
- vercel.json: remove legacy @secret env references (hard deploy blocker on
  modern Vercel: 'Secret does not exist'); keep security headers
- Build no longer requires any env vars: ClerkProvider wrapped conditionally
  in layout, middleware passes through without Clerk keys, Header hides auth
  UI when keyless, /dashboard renders as public demo when keyless
- middleware: await auth.protect() (Clerk v6 async API)
- lib/supabase: lazy getSupabase() instead of module-level non-null crash
- app/page.tsx: remove framer-motion + unused imports from server component
- dashboard: drop redirect to nonexistent /sign-in route
- Add .env.example (referenced by README but missing) and un-ignore it
- Footer: remove 9 dead social links and dead /legal/* routes
- #contact anchors now resolve (homepage section + mailto CTA)

Honesty repositioning (there is no product yet — the site now says so):
- Remove all fabricated claims: 200+ robots, 847 completed jobs, 94% Level 5
  rate, 4.1mo payback, fake testimonials labeled VERIFIED CASE, SOC 2 Type II
  / ISO 13849 PLd / WSIB certification claims, fake Procore/ACC integrations,
  fake fleet scarcity and lead times, fake enterprise customers
- Reposition as pre-launch founding pilot program recruiting GTA contractors
- Pricing reframed as disclosed target model; performance numbers labeled as
  design targets pending pilot validation
- ROI calculator rewritten with coherent math (manual baseline vs target RaaS
  rate) and disclosed assumptions; removed incoherent capex payback for a
  no-capex model
- Chatbot responses rewritten honestly; labeled as scripted, not live AI
- Dashboard clearly labeled product demo with sample data
- README rewritten with real setup instructions and pre-launch owner TODOs
